This article is a press gaggle by Press Secretary Josh Earnest, discussing President Obama's visit to Flint, Michigan. The President is joined by members of the Michigan congressional delegation and senior administration officials who have been involved in responding to the water crisis in Flint. The President will visit a food bank, meet with federal officials coordinating the response, and have a conversation with members of the community affected by the crisis. He will then deliver a speech to the community. The President will emphasize that he cares deeply about the challenges facing Flint and that the administration will continue to help mobilize resources for the city's recovery. The article also touches on the presidential election, with Earnest stating that the President will have an active role in supporting the Democratic nominee and making a case for the progress made during his presidency. Earnest also mentions the need for Congress to provide more funding to address the water crisis in Flint.